1
00:01:03,610 --> 00:01:05,016
You take it easy.

2
00:01:05,210 --> 00:01:07,989
I will tell you all the details
when my husband comes.

3
00:01:08,633 --> 00:01:10,496
Brother, why have they come?

4
00:01:10,918 --> 00:01:13,870
People living in the second plot
of land are troubled by cholera.

5
00:01:14,199 --> 00:01:15,730
People get scared and leave here.

6
00:01:16,128 --> 00:01:19,206
They have come to ask the husband for help.
- Another new question!

7
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:20,873
Mr. Das, after calling the headquarters….

8
00:01:20,953 --> 00:01:22,295
...find a way to
treat those people.

9
00:01:22,683 --> 00:01:24,309
I will go today and meet the
people in the second part...

10
00:01:24,372 --> 00:01:25,779
...because I won't be coming tomorrow.

11
00:01:25,859 --> 00:01:27,622
Tomorrow is my daughter's
birthday, let's hurry!

12
00:04:47,309 --> 00:04:49,393
Listen Charu,
Aunty has not come.

13
00:04:50,068 --> 00:04:52,472
The car that went to pick him up came from the station empty-handed. - What is that?

14
00:04:52,973 --> 00:04:56,390
He had said that he would come
to meet us on his way to Kashi.

15
00:04:56,625 --> 00:04:58,105
There must be some important work.

16
00:04:58,310 --> 00:05:02,105
Today is our daughter's first
birthday, but aunty can't come.

17
00:05:02,185 --> 00:05:04,225
The party will be boring without him.
- Yes.

18
00:05:05,279 --> 00:05:09,050
Although we were not related to
Aunty, more than our relatives...

19
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,865
...He loves us.

20
00:05:14,611 --> 00:05:16,254
Now is the time to feed the baby.

21
00:05:16,860 --> 00:05:18,900
Okay then, I'll get
dressed later to take him.

22
00:05:24,219 --> 00:05:26,610
Look at Rama's latest dress

23
00:05:26,908 --> 00:05:29,157
Sha!  It's very beautiful.

24
00:05:31,726 --> 00:05:33,723
Today is your daughter's
first birthday, isn't it?

25
00:05:33,983 --> 00:05:36,758
No, on your daughter's first birthday.

26
00:05:36,966 --> 00:05:39,915
And whose birthday is next year?
- Rama's other birthday.

27
00:05:40,068 --> 00:05:42,441
And only on Rama's
birthday every year?

28
00:05:44,431 --> 00:05:46,791
Please wait!  I can't take
care of this one child...

29
00:05:46,998 --> 00:05:49,429
I don't want any more.
- Gentleman!

30
00:05:51,739 --> 00:05:52,932
who

31
00:05:54,117 --> 00:05:57,343
what's the problem
- This child, sir

32
00:05:57,383 --> 00:06:00,164
Why what happened to that child?
- What's next?

33
00:06:00,248 --> 00:06:02,116
what are you saying
Whose child are you?

34
00:06:02,315 --> 00:06:04,097
This is the wife of the husband's worker.

35
00:06:05,111 --> 00:06:06,648
Why didn't he come to work today?

36
00:06:07,418 --> 00:06:09,471
He is dead, man.

37
00:06:09,684 --> 00:06:12,424
He and his wife
both died of cholera.

38
00:06:14,831 --> 00:06:16,152
Yes, this epidemic is
spreading everywhere.

39
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,764
So what brought this boy here?

40
00:06:20,151 --> 00:06:22,400
Now this child has no one, sir.

41
00:06:22,444 --> 00:06:25,368
Who will take care of this child?
- If you can sympathize with the husband...

42
00:06:25,448 --> 00:06:27,353
No way, guests will come
to our house in a little while.

43
00:06:27,526 --> 00:06:29,526
Go now and come back later.

44
00:06:32,999 --> 00:06:35,519
welcome  - How are you, uncle?

45
00:06:35,599 --> 00:06:38,279
how are you uncle  -
How are you, sister-in-law?

46
00:06:44,479 --> 00:06:47,094
Sha!  Very beautiful.

47
00:06:49,917 --> 00:06:51,087
Aya, take him away.

48
00:07:02,526 --> 00:07:07,441
I want an ice cream.
- Okay, I'll get you one.

49
00:07:07,863 --> 00:07:09,800
Badal!  Bring an ice cream.

50
00:07:17,986 --> 00:07:18,989
Listen!

51
00:07:20,654 --> 00:07:26,231
It's okay, son, don't cry.

52
00:07:37,952 --> 00:07:39,104
Get in, lady.

53
00:07:44,591 --> 00:07:45,791
bye Bye.

54
00:07:46,609 --> 00:07:49,134
why this  What are you still
doing here keeping the child?

55
00:07:49,273 --> 00:07:51,077
what's the problem
Whose child is this?

56
00:07:51,331 --> 00:07:53,407
These are the children of our worker.

57
00:07:53,567 --> 00:07:55,306
His mother and father
died of cholera this morning.

58
00:07:55,382 --> 00:07:57,128
There is nothing I can
do to take him away.

59
00:07:57,199 --> 00:08:00,187
We only have the help of
the husband, gentlemen.

60
00:08:03,303 --> 00:08:04,598
Here, take these ten rupees...

61
00:08:04,678 --> 00:08:05,810
...and find another home for him.

62
00:08:06,092 --> 00:08:09,026
Where should we take this baby, sir?  This
little one belongs to a very low caste.

63
00:08:09,375 --> 00:08:11,683
There is no one of this
child's caste in this village.

64
00:08:11,899 --> 00:08:13,017
Then take it to another village

65
00:08:13,211 --> 00:08:14,752
I am looking for
someone like that, sir, but

66
00:08:14,776 --> 00:08:16,316
until then, who will
take care of this Kelly?

67
00:08:16,665 --> 00:08:18,125
His mother and father are gone...

68
00:08:18,174 --> 00:08:21,082
Little by little, this child will
become food for vultures and foxes.

69
00:08:21,086 --> 00:08:23,261
I was able to save the girl
because I got there on time.

70
00:08:23,865 --> 00:08:24,958
Oh my god!

71
00:08:25,774 --> 00:08:28,629
Charu, who wants to put this
kind of trouble in the backyard?

72
00:08:28,779 --> 00:08:31,541
As good as they take him.
- Did you mean that?

73
00:08:32,907 --> 00:08:36,560
Is it good for those foxes and vultures to take him away? - No, I mean...

74
00:08:43,313 --> 00:08:46,174
Come on!  - Yes ma'am?

75
00:08:47,857 --> 00:08:50,630
Can you take care of this
child for two or three days?

76
00:08:50,774 --> 00:08:53,094
What's wrong Miss?
Am I in for it?

77
00:08:54,002 --> 00:08:55,372
Take him inside.

78
00:08:57,119 --> 00:08:58,796
Bathe him in hot water...

79
00:08:58,876 --> 00:09:00,750
...put on Rama's old dress.

80
00:09:01,293 --> 00:09:03,861
Keep him in your room.
- Yes, ma'am.

81
00:09:04,237 --> 00:09:05,914
You are very kind lady.

82
00:09:05,994 --> 00:09:10,780
Find someone of his caste as soon as possible. - Yes sir.

83
00:09:11,029 --> 00:09:12,474
It takes two or three days.

84
00:09:12,674 --> 00:09:14,910
I'll come back, sir, I'll come back, lady.
- Good.

85
00:12:15,997 --> 00:12:19,606
Is it Rama or Sujata who is crying?
- Sujata?

86
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,261
Yes, the other child.

87
00:12:21,826 --> 00:12:25,163
Oh, did you just name him?

88
00:12:25,243 --> 00:12:29,523
why?  Is that a bad name?
- No, not like that.

89
00:12:29,855 --> 00:12:33,270
It seems like a meaningless name.

90
00:12:33,937 --> 00:12:37,560
That child belongs to a very low
caste, but you named him Sujata.

91
00:12:38,628 --> 00:12:40,709
It just popped into my head.

92
00:12:45,414 --> 00:12:46,842
Who is coming in that cart?

93
00:12:50,982 --> 00:12:54,773
Charu!  It must be the aunt.
- Aunt?!

94
00:12:55,659 --> 00:12:58,720
how are you aunty  -
Hey, don't jump, kids!

95
00:13:00,369 --> 00:13:03,257
The leg is amputated.

96
00:13:03,718 --> 00:13:06,182
Because these are my
grandchildren, I have no freedom at all.

97
00:13:06,262 --> 00:13:09,924
He is very naughty.
- Both should be blessed.

98
00:13:10,004 --> 00:13:11,413
You didn't even come to
Rama's birthday party...

99
00:13:11,493 --> 00:13:12,869
...not even sent a letter.

100
00:13:13,140 --> 00:13:16,857
I was ready to come, but I
just looked at Litha and knew...

101
00:13:16,937 --> 00:13:19,034
...It was not an auspicious
moment, so I stayed away.

102
00:13:19,671 --> 00:13:22,826
He said that it is not good
to travel at such times.

103
00:13:23,457 --> 00:13:26,130
Get to know him
Bhavani Shankar Sharma.

104
00:13:26,401 --> 00:13:28,061
He is a very knowledgeable priest.

105
00:13:28,691 --> 00:13:30,624
Performing a Chandipat Pooja in the
month in which the girl child was born...

106
00:13:30,834 --> 00:13:32,278
...Good for that kid's future.

107
00:13:32,466 --> 00:13:34,952
That's why I called
him to come with us.

108
00:13:35,090 --> 00:13:37,520
Praise be to the priest.
- Goodbye!

109
00:13:38,904 --> 00:13:41,344
This lady did not introduce me properly.

110
00:13:42,019 --> 00:13:45,994
Actually, I am not a priest,
but a professor of English.

111
00:13:46,691 --> 00:13:49,055
I do Chandipat Pujas
because of my passion...

112
00:13:49,298 --> 00:13:51,856
...And those who spend time righteously...

113
00:13:52,354 --> 00:13:55,453
...to happiness.

114
00:13:56,149 --> 00:13:59,084
I've been sick lately.

115
00:13:59,558 --> 00:14:02,387
So I thought it would be better if I
went somewhere with a different climate...

116
00:14:02,467 --> 00:14:04,623
...And then he himself
invited me to come here.

117
00:14:04,703 --> 00:14:06,661
That's why I came.  - Very good.

118
00:14:07,037 --> 00:14:08,617
Stay here as long as you like.

119
00:14:08,794 --> 00:14:15,850
I pray that your fortunes
will improve as well as mine.

120
00:14:16,652 --> 00:14:20,080
Like a good son, do I
have water to take a bath?

121
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:22,525
All this dust is on my body.

122
00:14:22,605 --> 00:14:25,515
Go and get him some water to bathe.
- Come on sir.

123
00:14:25,595 --> 00:14:27,314
Go with him.  - Okay.

124
00:14:29,151 --> 00:14:30,325
Come in aunty.

125
00:14:32,338 --> 00:14:36,634
Come on, kids.
- Show me the child, what was your name?

126
00:14:36,778 --> 00:14:41,040
Rama.
- Rama?  Sha!  It is a very beautiful name.

127
00:14:41,864 --> 00:14:45,169
Wait Charu, I will bring
this river water from God.

128
00:14:45,962 --> 00:14:46,984
Come on.

129
00:14:50,917 --> 00:14:53,739
Charu, you know how Aunty is.

130
00:14:54,066 --> 00:14:56,657
He really thinks about that caste.

131
00:14:57,080 --> 00:15:00,673
Tell Aya to keep that child away.
Aunty should not be allowed to see him.

132
00:15:09,830 --> 00:15:13,907
Is this my son's daughter?
Wait, I'll take him over a bit.

133
00:15:13,987 --> 00:15:19,040
But... he...
- Do you think about him more than his mother?

134
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:23,277
Very beautiful,
just like her mother.

135
00:15:23,423 --> 00:15:27,514
Born!  Your daughter is very lucky.

136
00:15:27,594 --> 00:15:31,552
Give him to Aya.
- Your daughter is very beautiful.

137
00:15:31,725 --> 00:15:34,062
You will not have to
worry about his marriage.

138
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:36,967
Look how he laughs with me.

139
00:15:37,047 --> 00:15:38,353
Maybe he recognized me.

140
00:15:53,824 --> 00:15:55,670
Who can be heard crying inside

141
00:15:55,790 --> 00:15:57,689
Did you have twins?

142
00:15:59,757 --> 00:16:02,142
You didn't even tell me that.
- We didn't get twins.

143
00:16:02,228 --> 00:16:05,772
That is our daughter, Rama.
- Then who is this?

144
00:16:06,933 --> 00:16:09,581
Both his mother and
father are dead so we...

145
00:16:09,709 --> 00:16:11,591
But he must be from
a high caste, right?

146
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:16,693
No, he is low caste.
- Low caste?

147
00:16:16,773 --> 00:16:20,657
Eya Upen, I didn't expect
anything like this from you.

148
00:16:20,737 --> 00:16:22,778
You belong to a good and important family.
- But aunty...

149
00:16:22,858 --> 00:16:23,788
I don't want to hear anything.

150
00:16:23,868 --> 00:16:26,068
If I knew, inside this house...

151
00:16:26,148 --> 00:16:29,969
...I won't even step foot here
because you are keeping a low caste girl.

152
00:16:30,049 --> 00:16:31,612
Please listen to this aunty...

153
00:16:32,837 --> 00:16:34,632
Auntie, now you know the whole story.

154
00:16:35,199 --> 00:16:38,005
Now tell me what you would
do if you were in our place?

155
00:16:39,462 --> 00:16:42,260
What I thought was unfair...

156
00:16:42,712 --> 00:16:44,018
...I still see it that way.

157
00:16:44,098 --> 00:16:46,293
But aunty it's...
- Upen!

158
00:16:46,692 --> 00:16:49,180
Don't argue with me for having
read an English book or two!

159
00:16:50,743 --> 00:16:54,219
Man, that man is leaving.
- Going to go?

160
00:16:59,930 --> 00:17:02,803
Priest, why what?

161
00:17:04,274 --> 00:17:06,352
what's the problem

162
00:17:06,652 --> 00:17:09,760
All this is God's will.

163
00:17:10,159 --> 00:17:13,777
I want to go when I want to go.

164
00:17:14,351 --> 00:17:17,680
Aya told me and I saw
with my own eyes...

165
00:17:17,836 --> 00:17:21,625
...that you keep a low
caste child in your house.

166
00:17:21,860 --> 00:17:24,729
That's amazing!
Is that where you're going?

167
00:17:25,052 --> 00:17:27,231
There is nothing surprising about that.

168
00:17:27,668 --> 00:17:30,193
Our religion has...

169
00:17:30,273 --> 00:17:32,567
...It is not to catch a
low caste to keep with us.

170
00:17:33,227 --> 00:17:35,126
You are a very knowledgeable person.

171
00:17:35,582 --> 00:17:40,267
You must know that it is
also said in science - what?

172
00:17:40,909 --> 00:17:43,893
A gas is released from the
bodies of those low castes.

173
00:17:44,305 --> 00:17:48,258
It pollutes the bodies and
souls of important people like us.

174
00:17:48,435 --> 00:17:49,985
Have you seen the said gas?

175
00:17:51,243 --> 00:17:53,856
Did you know that food contains vitamins?
- Yes.

176
00:17:54,511 --> 00:17:57,390
Have you seen that vitamin?
- No.

177
00:17:57,842 --> 00:18:00,109
Does that mean that
food contains vitamins?

178
00:18:02,142 --> 00:18:03,807
OK, I'm going now.

179
00:18:04,298 --> 00:18:06,281
You asked me to stay...

180
00:18:06,538 --> 00:18:08,508
...But it's my misfortune
that I can't stay longer.

181
00:18:08,885 --> 00:18:10,879
Have a good trip.

182
00:18:15,067 --> 00:18:16,781
The priest got angry and left.

183
00:18:17,055 --> 00:18:21,682
Please stop him aunty.
- Now he won't stop when we say so.

184
00:18:22,298 --> 00:18:26,089
I know him very well
and he is very pious.

185
00:18:26,727 --> 00:18:31,115
I can put up with your
rude behavior but he won't.

186
00:18:31,570 --> 00:18:32,806
What do we do now?

187
00:18:32,886 --> 00:18:35,091
Get rid of this problem
as soon as possible.

188
00:18:35,955 --> 00:18:38,170
I say this for your own good.

189
00:18:38,722 --> 00:18:41,437
I have no problem with that,
I will go to Kashi tomorrow.

190
00:18:47,024 --> 00:18:49,794
Why are you so quiet?
- What should I do?

191
00:18:49,853 --> 00:18:51,801
I started to feel scared too

192
00:18:51,881 --> 00:18:54,352
Because that priest said about a gas?

193
00:18:54,432 --> 00:19:00,104
No, no, it's not. I
hope we won't suffer.

194
00:19:00,245 --> 00:19:02,092
We don't want to suffer...

195
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:06,236
...But those who do injustice in the
name of religion will suffer the same.

196
00:19:06,259 --> 00:19:08,402
Don't laugh at every question.

197
00:19:09,004 --> 00:19:12,467
Aunt also thinks that we will
get rid of this girl's problem soon.

198
00:19:13,544 --> 00:19:16,590
Listen, tell the guard
to take him away.

199
00:19:25,007 --> 00:19:30,096
Ah, is this Sujata? Nice little kelly. Look at her beauty...
- Aya!

200
00:19:35,135 --> 00:19:36,494
Why did you touch him?

201
00:19:36,574 --> 00:19:40,059
Ah, if I touch him, will I lose
my caste?  Then I'll take a shower.

202
00:19:45,146 --> 00:19:46,936
No, this is no joke.

203
00:19:47,077 --> 00:19:49,920
You are getting too close to him.
- So that's the point?

204
00:19:50,558 --> 00:19:53,162
Don't worry Charu I
have prepared everything.

205
00:19:53,578 --> 00:19:55,456
What did you prepare?
- The guard told me...

206
00:19:55,536 --> 00:19:57,417
...that he found someone
from Sujata's caste.

207
00:19:57,457 --> 00:19:59,687
He will come tomorrow and take Sujata.

208
00:20:01,417 --> 00:20:04,095
Charu, do we have a bamboo shoot in our house?
- Yes why?

209
00:20:04,370 --> 00:20:06,973
Aya told me that Kelly had a little fever.
- Bamboo?

210
00:20:07,827 --> 00:20:11,707
A fever is spreading in
this area, take care of him.

211
00:20:18,326 --> 00:20:20,697
Yes, he has a fever.

212
00:20:22,302 --> 00:20:24,685
I saw that you also touched him
and now you have to take a bath too.

213
00:20:29,037 --> 00:20:30,742
So you tested me, didn't you?

214
00:20:38,828 --> 00:20:41,599
Charu, it's not our fault.

215
00:20:42,582 --> 00:20:45,021
People also get closer to the animals they raise.

216
00:20:45,739 --> 00:20:47,837
But he is a human child.

217
00:20:51,704 --> 00:20:54,044
Will I be able to do my job?

218
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:56,458
Yes, yes they can.

219
00:21:05,782 --> 00:21:07,531
Charu, the guard...

220
00:21:07,611 --> 00:21:09,579
...Sujata has brought
a man to give.

221
00:21:10,557 --> 00:21:11,421
Mr.

222
00:21:22,696 --> 00:21:23,560
Mr

223
00:21:27,500 --> 00:21:28,419
Mr.

224
00:21:30,107 --> 00:21:30,964
Hello sir.

225
00:21:31,708 --> 00:21:35,409
I brought someone from the
girl's caste to hand over the child.

226
00:21:35,554 --> 00:21:38,282
What should I do?
Tell Aya to bring the child.

227
00:21:41,173 --> 00:21:44,737
Come on!  Come on!  Bring that kid.

228
00:22:01,892 --> 00:22:02,737
here

229
00:22:03,132 --> 00:22:04,323
Take this girl.

230
00:22:06,352 --> 00:22:09,208
What can I do if I
only take this girl?

231
00:22:10,338 --> 00:22:13,069
Don't forget what we decided.

232
00:22:14,716 --> 00:22:20,500
First I need money, next I need
clothes, I need clothes for washing.

233
00:22:20,624 --> 00:22:23,949
Why am I just accepting this girl?

234
00:22:24,029 --> 00:22:26,185
Do you think I'm stupid?

235
00:22:26,265 --> 00:22:27,451
listen...

236
00:22:27,881 --> 00:22:31,259
are you drunk  - Why...
- Why are you afraid?

237
00:22:31,339 --> 00:22:34,756
Tell him I'm drunk, I
drank with my money.

238
00:22:35,664 --> 00:22:39,597
Why do I put myself through
this kind of misery without money?

239
00:22:40,824 --> 00:22:42,560
Get that drunk off this land!

240
00:22:42,972 --> 00:22:45,434
Guards, take him away!

241
00:22:45,974 --> 00:22:48,242
Be a man before
you take a child.

242
00:22:48,298 --> 00:22:50,525
You will spend all the money
given to you on drinking.

243
00:22:50,611 --> 00:22:52,892
Get him out.

244
00:22:54,362 --> 00:22:56,321
Take the girl inside again.
- That's right.

245
00:22:59,262 --> 00:23:02,698
That's fine, we can't
give him to a lowly drunk.

246
00:23:03,092 --> 00:23:05,452
But we better give
him to someone soon.

247
00:23:06,674 --> 00:23:09,478
He is still a child.
But when he grows up?

248
00:23:10,065 --> 00:23:13,491
No, it is better to stay
away from such relationships.

249
00:23:13,865 --> 00:23:15,304
But where do you put him?

250
00:23:16,132 --> 00:23:17,886
We are going to leave here soon.

251
00:23:18,534 --> 00:23:22,218
Let's find a good family for him

252
00:23:41,834 --> 00:23:45,696
Rama!  Sujata!
Come and drink this milk.

253
00:23:48,118 --> 00:23:50,554
why did you fall for
me  - You fell yourself.

254
00:23:50,692 --> 00:23:54,634
Liar, I won't talk again.
- it's OK.

255
00:23:55,606 --> 00:23:56,492
I'm leaving.

256
00:24:09,449 --> 00:24:11,194
Mommy!  Daddy!

257
00:24:12,235 --> 00:24:15,074
It will fall down from
there. Go down quickly.

258
00:24:15,305 --> 00:24:17,034
Mom!  Dad!

259
00:24:17,298 --> 00:24:19,357
Don't be bad kids, go play.

260
00:24:21,632 --> 00:24:23,381
Looks like he's back...

261
00:24:23,461 --> 00:24:25,208
...Sujatha has been taught
to call us mom and dad.

262
00:24:25,512 --> 00:24:27,976
Is it true, or is it...

263
00:24:28,056 --> 00:24:29,792
...As Rama says, mommy and daddy say.

264
00:24:30,949 --> 00:24:33,124
I don't talk to you
I don't talk to you

265
00:24:33,517 --> 00:24:35,150
don't talk to me
don't talk to me

266
00:24:35,664 --> 00:24:37,149
Don't talk to me!

267
00:24:39,229 --> 00:24:41,294
You don't have a mommy.
- You don't have a mother either.

268
00:24:41,374 --> 00:24:43,664
You don't even have a father.
- You don't even have a father.

269
00:24:46,580 --> 00:24:48,927
Listen, you told me...

270
00:24:49,364 --> 00:24:51,760
...As soon as we get here,
let's hand it over to someone.

271
00:24:52,514 --> 00:24:54,744
Now it's been four years since we came here.

272
00:24:54,748 --> 00:24:56,233
But Sujata still...

273
00:24:56,313 --> 00:24:58,218
I tried hard but we have
responsibility for him.

274
00:24:58,227 --> 00:25:02,407
Neither you nor I want to
give him away to anyone

275
00:25:03,320 --> 00:25:04,471
That is true.

276
00:25:08,051 --> 00:25:09,991
Can't we send him to hell?

277
00:25:11,195 --> 00:25:14,040
From now Sujata is trying
to match Rama in everything.

278
00:25:14,361 --> 00:25:16,680
When he grows up, we will
have to face many problems.

279
00:25:17,355 --> 00:25:19,166
OK, I'll find a good orphanage.

280
00:25:19,275 --> 00:25:21,459
And what about Rama's learning?

281
00:25:21,596 --> 00:25:23,130
I spoke to a good teacher.

282
00:25:23,301 --> 00:25:25,261
He will come to teach from tomorrow.
- Daddy!

283
00:25:26,578 --> 00:25:29,550
Dad, do you eat halwa?
- Do you eat some too?

284
00:25:29,821 --> 00:25:31,628
here

285
00:25:38,508 --> 00:25:41,646
what are you eating  - Halva.
- What?

286
00:25:42,498 --> 00:25:44,480
Don't you know what halwa is?

287
00:25:45,493 --> 00:25:47,613
He always fights with Rama.

288
00:25:48,283 --> 00:25:50,995
Aya told me that she used
to beat Rama sometimes.

289
00:25:51,075 --> 00:25:52,511
They are still children.

290
00:25:52,932 --> 00:25:55,631
Dad!  Don't I have halwa?

291
00:25:58,252 --> 00:25:59,464
come come come here

292
00:26:09,694 --> 00:26:11,231
Don't eat with that spoon.
- why?

293
00:26:11,670 --> 00:26:13,120
Without thinking that he is low caste...

294
00:26:13,452 --> 00:26:14,991
...do you eat what he left?

295
00:26:22,050 --> 00:26:25,130
Sujata take this flour,
can we make puri with it?

296
00:26:25,210 --> 00:26:26,850
Yes we can.

297
00:26:30,090 --> 00:26:33,861
Rama!  Here is a new book
and a stone tablet for you.

298
00:26:33,941 --> 00:26:36,050
Come and learn from your teacher

299
00:26:36,130 --> 00:26:39,650
Where is my book, I do not study?
- No, you play.

300
00:26:46,558 --> 00:26:49,531
Why did you buy the book Sujata?
- I am also studying.

301
00:26:49,611 --> 00:26:52,623
Don't touch these books, your
father will be angry with me.

302
00:27:01,077 --> 00:27:04,028
Brother Bahadur!
Give me a book and I will read.

303
00:27:04,108 --> 00:27:06,666
a book?
I don't have any books, children.

304
00:27:06,746 --> 00:27:09,877
Liar!  Why lie?
There is a book.

305
00:27:10,104 --> 00:27:13,402
But that is Ramayana.
- Okay, then I will read the Ramayana.

306
00:27:15,423 --> 00:27:18,293
Sit down!
I will tell you a beautiful story.

307
00:27:18,373 --> 00:27:20,925
Teacher, I will also
learn here is my book.

308
00:27:21,454 --> 00:27:23,346
Are you going to study such a big book?
- Yes.

309
00:27:23,426 --> 00:27:27,250
Come on Sujata, you can't stay here.
- No, I'm studying too.

310
00:27:27,330 --> 00:27:30,954
Listen up kids.
- not!  Let me go!  Let me go!

311
00:27:31,034 --> 00:27:33,170
Come here... - Let go...
- Why what happened?

312
00:27:33,930 --> 00:27:36,752
Look, father, he
won't let me study.

313
00:27:36,925 --> 00:27:39,585
Go and go and learn.

314
00:27:47,325 --> 00:27:50,085
Who did the letter come from?
- Oh!  Charu?

315
00:27:50,504 --> 00:27:53,574
I have received a reply to the
letter I sent to that anathagar.

316
00:27:53,654 --> 00:27:55,542
They like to accept Sujata.

317
00:27:56,861 --> 00:27:58,947
This orphanage is very famous.

318
00:27:59,628 --> 00:28:01,325
There will be no
problem for Sujata.

319
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:05,325
it is good.

320
00:28:05,855 --> 00:28:09,617
Take two or three
days off and let him go.

321
00:28:11,195 --> 00:28:16,150
No, I'm too busy
to take a vacation.

322
00:28:16,837 --> 00:28:24,006
And then?  Just ask the
teacher, he will like it...

323
00:28:24,611 --> 00:28:25,855
OK, I'll ask him

324
00:28:31,639 --> 00:28:34,968
OK, I'll take care
of that, don't worry!

325
00:28:35,448 --> 00:28:36,888
I will drop him off there.

326
00:28:37,250 --> 00:28:39,613
Please meet the manager
of the orphanage...

327
00:28:39,693 --> 00:28:43,022
...Tell him to take
good care of Sujata.

328
00:28:43,401 --> 00:28:46,808
Money is not a problem, I'll
give whatever I want - OK.

329
00:28:50,363 --> 00:28:54,688
Teacher!  I want to talk to you.
- Say yes.

330
00:28:55,542 --> 00:28:57,808
Sujata has become very friendly to us.

331
00:28:58,947 --> 00:29:01,248
Please, make him go anyway.

332
00:29:01,888 --> 00:29:05,217
He doesn't want to know, we are
doing this to keep him away from us.

333
00:29:05,866 --> 00:29:07,066
Very good

334
00:29:08,710 --> 00:29:10,888
Is it true, teacher?
- Of course children

335
00:29:11,262 --> 00:29:14,521
That beautiful
place is far away...

336
00:29:14,601 --> 00:29:19,008
...where heaven and earth meet.

337
00:29:19,476 --> 00:29:21,942
You will love to see it.

338
00:29:22,488 --> 00:29:25,099
There are silver trees
with golden leaves...

339
00:29:25,812 --> 00:29:28,472
...They are on top and
the Kottori are always short.

340
00:30:18,669 --> 00:30:21,556
Would you like to go to that country?
- Yes, I would like to.

341
00:30:21,848 --> 00:30:25,967
I am taking Rama with me.
- No children, go alone for now.

342
00:30:26,670 --> 00:30:28,168
Then you can come back...

343
00:30:28,248 --> 00:30:30,420
...surprise everyone
with the beauty there.

344
00:30:31,069 --> 00:30:33,816
We can take Rama later.  - Okay.

345
00:30:34,681 --> 00:30:40,594
Listen!  Listen!  Children,
be ready at five this evening.

346
00:30:41,468 --> 00:30:42,787
I will bring a car.  - Okay.

347
00:30:52,570 --> 00:30:56,322
Charu!  The teacher said that
Sujata is ready to go to the orphanage.

348
00:30:56,841 --> 00:30:58,701
He will pick her up
at five o'clock today.

349
00:30:58,781 --> 00:31:00,225
Have everything ready.

350
00:31:01,328 --> 00:31:03,589
Listen!  Today at the office I...

351
00:31:03,669 --> 00:31:05,890
...I have a special
job, it will be late.

352
00:31:22,051 --> 00:31:23,517
Dad!

353
00:31:26,322 --> 00:31:27,727
Here's your hat.

354
00:31:28,105 --> 00:31:30,754
You carry this all the time;
Why did you forget today?

355
00:31:30,834 --> 00:31:34,214
If I didn't remind you, you
will have to work in the sun.

356
00:31:34,294 --> 00:31:35,608
Yes Sujata.

357
00:32:29,618 --> 00:32:32,788
sujata are you ready

358
00:32:35,001 --> 00:32:36,948
Yes, Master.  - Come on

359
00:32:51,942 --> 00:32:54,201
Teacher, father is not coming?
- not

360
00:32:54,460 --> 00:32:56,698
And mother?  - No...
- Then I won't go.

361
00:32:56,778 --> 00:33:03,508
Listen children, your parents, Rama
and all three have already left for there.

362
00:33:03,735 --> 00:33:05,627
They sent me to get you.
- really?

363
00:33:05,707 --> 00:33:07,465
Yes.
- Then I will come with you.

364
00:33:17,617 --> 00:33:19,725
Mother, mother!

365
00:33:20,817 --> 00:33:25,487
There are sweets and dolls in that world.
- I don't want them.

366
00:33:25,567 --> 00:33:27,368
Listen Sujata...
- Mother!

367
00:33:29,390 --> 00:33:32,613
Mom!  Mom!

368
00:33:32,693 --> 00:33:34,926
Mom!  Mom!

369
00:33:36,623 --> 00:33:38,959
Mom, the teacher is very bad.

370
00:33:39,143 --> 00:33:41,585
He tried to trick me and
take me somewhere else.

371
00:33:41,721 --> 00:33:43,433
I will not learn from him from today.

372
00:33:44,925 --> 00:33:47,498
are you crying mom?  do not Cry.

373
00:33:47,801 --> 00:33:51,130
I will never leave you anywhere!

374
00:33:58,923 --> 00:34:01,420
Maybe Sujata would know.  - Yes.

375
00:34:02,302 --> 00:34:04,501
I wanted to see him when he was gone.

376
00:34:05,236 --> 00:34:09,213
I made a mistake.
- Why do you call it a mistake?

377
00:34:10,478 --> 00:34:12,822
There is nothing wrong with
that, you are like his mother.

378
00:34:13,440 --> 00:34:15,191
Maybe this is God's will.

379
00:34:16,347 --> 00:34:17,821
We have been several times before...

380
00:34:17,901 --> 00:34:20,802
...Sujatha tried to keep away
from our lives but it didn't work.

381
00:34:21,927 --> 00:34:24,748
If he thinks this is his
home, let him stay like this.

382
00:34:25,515 --> 00:34:27,224
When he grows up...

383
00:34:27,655 --> 00:34:30,685
...God's blessings will
pave a different way for us.

384
00:34:32,521 --> 00:34:35,861
Listen!  You get angry
when you hear this.

385
00:34:36,369 --> 00:34:38,131
I was ordered to another shift.

386
00:34:38,380 --> 00:34:40,153
What forest are we going to this time?

387
00:34:40,521 --> 00:34:44,272
Prepare things for the
long journey to Dehradun.

388
00:36:19,646 --> 00:36:21,139
No one can be seen.

389
00:36:21,863 --> 00:36:24,025
We have not come to see
our aunt for many years.

390
00:36:24,566 --> 00:36:26,371
We came today without even informing him.

391
00:36:27,085 --> 00:36:28,783
I don't know if he will understand us.

392
00:36:28,988 --> 00:36:30,426
Why doesn't he understand us?

393
00:36:40,836 --> 00:36:42,080
Listen!

394
00:36:45,766 --> 00:36:47,874
who are you  - Didn't catch me?

395
00:36:48,133 --> 00:36:51,258
You came to our house once.
- just wait.

396
00:36:51,442 --> 00:36:54,923
I can't hear very well
until I put on my glasses.

397
00:36:57,259 --> 00:36:59,237
Remember once you came to Madhupur?

398
00:36:59,658 --> 00:37:03,085
Yes, yes Jabalpur eh?
- No, Madhupur, Madhupur!

399
00:37:03,165 --> 00:37:08,480
Oh!  Madhupur!
- Hey!  born  Charu?

400
00:37:10,599 --> 00:37:12,177
God bless you!

401
00:37:12,587 --> 00:37:15,406
You have remembered
your aunt for a long time.

402
00:37:16,154 --> 00:37:17,720
Come on, let's go upstairs.

403
00:37:17,930 --> 00:37:19,930
You are still that low caste girl...

404
00:37:20,010 --> 00:37:21,374
...wasn't sent from home, was it?

405
00:37:21,450 --> 00:37:22,952
Did you bring him this far?

406
00:37:23,032 --> 00:37:26,216
I couldn't get rid of that orphan
girl, she got very close to us.

407
00:37:26,296 --> 00:37:29,989
Don't say such things!
Your family is very important.

408
00:37:30,335 --> 00:37:32,930
You belong to an important generation.
- What shall we do, aunt?

409
00:37:33,469 --> 00:37:35,930
I thought it was our helplessness.
- Sha!

410
00:37:36,940 --> 00:37:38,290
It is not a matter of forgiveness.

411
00:37:38,789 --> 00:37:41,200
You lived in forests and mountains...

412
00:37:41,524 --> 00:37:43,730
...There was no one to
gossip about them at that time.

413
00:37:43,810 --> 00:37:47,038
But now you are
back in your society.

414
00:37:47,535 --> 00:37:49,816
You have to follow the rules in this.

415
00:37:50,660 --> 00:37:52,508
If you keep that low
caste girl at home...

416
00:37:52,588 --> 00:37:55,686
...It also affects Rama's marriage.

417
00:37:56,216 --> 00:37:57,978
That problem came to me too, aunty.

418
00:37:58,281 --> 00:38:01,135
But what can we do?  We are helpless.
- No...

419
00:38:01,215 --> 00:38:05,427
Where is Adir?  Can't see
the man, isn't he at home?

420
00:38:06,050 --> 00:38:10,465
What to say about him?
He went to a city library.

421
00:38:11,027 --> 00:38:13,254
He has his own
library in this house...

422
00:38:13,481 --> 00:38:15,221
...but that's not enough for them.

423
00:38:15,589 --> 00:38:19,373
MA  Even after passing the exam,
this boy's learning has not stopped

424
00:38:20,086 --> 00:38:22,150
Learning never ends, aunty.

425
00:38:22,594 --> 00:38:26,163
So we will go now.
- Be careful.  - God bless you.

426
00:38:45,911 --> 00:38:49,879
Son!  Where is Sujata?
- What time is it now?

427
00:38:49,959 --> 00:38:52,993
I don't know how to watch the time.
- It's 4:30.

428
00:38:53,394 --> 00:38:56,032
At this time, he is
collecting clothes upstairs.

429
00:39:00,346 --> 00:39:04,237
Sujata!  - Why Bahadur brother?

430
00:39:06,285 --> 00:39:08,047
Isn't it tea time?

431
00:39:08,382 --> 00:39:11,916
Tell the cook to put the
kettle on;  I will come soon.

432
00:39:12,489 --> 00:39:14,727
The sugar is gone.
Shall I go get it?

433
00:39:14,807 --> 00:39:17,332
No brother, I sent Basant to the shop.

434
00:39:17,526 --> 00:39:18,499
He will come soon.

435
00:39:18,579 --> 00:39:22,231
Nothing can escape
my girl's eyes.

436
00:42:36,576 --> 00:42:40,814
To tell you the truth, my head is very
confused because of my aunt's story.

437
00:42:41,344 --> 00:42:42,662
Rama's wedding...

438
00:42:42,846 --> 00:42:45,777
What will we do if we have to
face problems because of Sujata?

439
00:42:46,274 --> 00:42:48,555
Nothing to worry about?

440
00:42:48,912 --> 00:42:50,858
You won't have any problems.

441
00:42:51,171 --> 00:42:52,913
If our relatives ask about
our relationship with Sujata...

442
00:42:52,993 --> 00:42:55,270
...What is our answer?

443
00:42:55,659 --> 00:42:58,081
Some people already asked.

444
00:42:58,967 --> 00:43:00,437
Listen, Sujata!

445
00:43:00,762 --> 00:43:03,248
Call me sister and I will ask.

446
00:43:03,453 --> 00:43:07,052
Ok ok sister!  - Why what?

447
00:43:07,377 --> 00:43:11,171
These look great.
- Is that what called me?

448
00:43:11,251 --> 00:43:13,106
No, to something else

449
00:43:15,842 --> 00:43:17,021
Why did you do that?

450
00:43:17,101 --> 00:43:19,225
Don't you remember you hit me yesterday?

451
00:43:19,549 --> 00:43:21,312
Is that too?  wait

452
00:43:21,392 --> 00:43:25,016
I will give tea to father and mother
and teach them a good lesson.

453
00:43:26,642 --> 00:43:29,416
We can marry him but who...

454
00:43:29,496 --> 00:43:31,755
...marrying a low caste
girl without education?

455
00:43:31,835 --> 00:43:33,416
If he is uneducated like that...

456
00:43:33,496 --> 00:43:35,016
...we have to be responsible for it.

457
00:43:36,901 --> 00:43:38,416
Is it tea time yet?

458
00:43:39,377 --> 00:43:41,172
Sujata, you are the watch of this house.

459
00:43:41,252 --> 00:43:43,994
Dad, Mom made a great cake today.

460
00:43:44,074 --> 00:43:46,031
Not me, you made it.

461
00:43:46,111 --> 00:43:48,736
If you didn't tell me how to
do it, I wouldn't be able to do it.

462
00:43:48,946 --> 00:43:50,616
Never mind, I'll fix it.

463
00:43:55,659 --> 00:43:59,136
Charu, there are women's
welfare ashrams, right?

464
00:43:59,410 --> 00:44:02,701
If we take their help, won't Sujata
be able to find someone suitable?

465
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:04,416
It doesn't matter what his caste is...

466
00:44:04,687 --> 00:44:06,087
...If he has studied,
if he has a job...

467
00:44:06,167 --> 00:44:08,776
...or if you have a small business.

468
00:44:09,110 --> 00:44:12,016
Anyone can find God if they try.

469
00:44:12,644 --> 00:44:15,985
What if we pay a large dowry?

470
00:44:16,065 --> 00:44:17,416
If that happens, there
will be no problem.

471
00:44:17,746 --> 00:44:20,904
Anyone would love to
marry a girl like Sujata.

472
00:44:23,823 --> 00:44:27,499
Who is home?
Is this the eighth house?

473
00:44:31,499 --> 00:44:34,591
This is the eighth house.
- I want to meet you.  - I am born.

474
00:44:34,937 --> 00:44:37,477
Oh, are you...
- I can't understand you.

475
00:44:37,650 --> 00:44:39,229
you don't know me

476
00:44:39,467 --> 00:44:40,829
Is Charu at home?

477
00:44:41,251 --> 00:44:44,245
I am his uncle.  - Ah, come in.

478
00:44:45,617 --> 00:44:47,261
Uncle, you?

479
00:44:47,434 --> 00:44:50,007
Come on, come on.
- Charu, are you okay?

480
00:44:50,087 --> 00:44:51,044
sit down

481
00:44:51,124 --> 00:44:54,569
Sha!  You have
prepared tea for me.

482
00:44:56,797 --> 00:45:00,029
Charu where are your children?

483
00:45:00,699 --> 00:45:02,354
Uncle, God gave me only one child

484
00:45:02,434 --> 00:45:03,975
Talk to him.

485
00:45:04,224 --> 00:45:05,835
I want to see him.

486
